ASD_Processing_GSE50759_Final

Project Goal: to investigate whether the 94-CpG pediatric buccal clock shows a deviation in estimate in individuals effected with Autism Spectrum Disorder. Going to look at the cohort “GSE50759”

https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE50759 Berko ER, Suzuki M, Beren F, Lemetre C et al. Mosaic epigenetic dysregulation of ectodermal cells in autism spectrum disorder. PLoS Genet 2014;10(5):e1004402. PMID: 24875834

Notes: This analysis is separate from the GSE50759 Preprocessing because that was for selecting only typically developing <20 year old samples specifically for being part of the test dataset. From that script, we identified some samples to remove for which we will also remove in this study, not all of them, because we want to include the ASD cases.

In the test data, we only included 32 samples. However, some filtering was done PRIOR to selecting only TD cases: Started with n=96 -12 had low buccal counts -2 were “other” outliers -1 was a sex mismatch

This left me with 81 samples, which I then removed all ASD cases, this left me with 42 TD. I then removed 8 samples because they were over 20 years old, then I removed 2 samples because they did not have exact age. Left with 32 samples.

Okay, so based on previous processing of this dataset we are going to remove the following samples: -2 outliers (“7668610064_R01C02”, “7676960015_R05C02”) -1 sex mismatch (7676960039_R03C01) -8 samples over 20 years old (“6229076093_R04C02” “7668610037_R02C01” “7668610064_R02C02” “7668610064_R05C02” “7676960015_R03C02” “7676960041_R01C01” “7676960041_R03C01” “7676960040_R06C01”) -2 that did not have exact age (“7676960039_R06C01”, “7676960040_R02C02”)

In summary, going to remove 13 samples, this will leave us with 83.

now propensity score matching

GSE_81 <- droplevels(GSE_81)

#look into sibship stuff - family ID is repeated for individuals, operating under the assumption that multiple people for same family...
GSE_81$Family <-  gsub("_.*$","",GSE_81$source_name_ch1)
GSE_81$Family <- as.factor(GSE_81$Family)
GSE_81$Case1 <- gsub("2","0",as.numeric(as.factor(GSE_81$Case)))
GSE_81_sub1 <- GSE_81[,c("Case1","ped94Age", "FinalAge2", "Buccal", "SentrixID", "BioSex", "CEU")]
GSE_81_sub2 <- GSE_81_sub1[complete.cases(GSE_81_sub1),]
dim(GSE_81_sub2) #81,8
MATCH_out <- matchit(Case1 ~ FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex+CEU,
                      method="nearest", distance="logit", discard="both",
                      ratio=2, caliper=.25,order="largest",data = GSE_81_sub2)
sum_match <- summary(MATCH_out, interactions=T, standardize=T)
sum_match  ### only 22 and 17 matched
wt <- MATCH_out$weights
GSE_81_match_data <- GSE_81_sub2[wt>0,]
dim(GSE_81_match_data) #39, 8
summary(lm(ped94Age ~ Case+FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex+CEU, data = GSE_81)) #p=0.01168 
summary(lm(ped94Age ~ Case1+FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex+CEU, data = GSE_81_match_data)) #0.03, can't add family as a covariate because too many levels: "ALL 37 residuals are 0: no residual degrees of freedom!”"

GSE_81_match_data$AgeAccelRes_Matched_Corrected <- summary(lm(ped94Age ~ FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex+CEU, data = GSE_81_match_data))$residuals
#need to change 0 and 1 to ASD and TD, respectively because it plots naturally with 1 on the right but we want ASD on the left for consistency 
#CASE: 1 = ASD, 0 = TD
GSE_81_match_data$Case2 <- gsub("1","ASD", GSE_81_match_data$Case1)
GSE_81_match_data$Case2 <- gsub("0","TD", GSE_81_match_data$Case2)
GSE_81_match_data$Case2 <- as.factor(GSE_81_match_data$Case2)
ggplot(GSE_81_match_data, aes(Case2, AgeAccelRes_Matched_Corrected))+
        geom_boxplot()+
        geom_point()

#now do propensity score matching on data without sibs:        
GSE_67_nosibs_sub1 <- GSE_67_nosibs[,c("Case1","ped94Age", "FinalAge2", "Buccal", "SentrixID", "BioSex", "CEU")]
GSE_67_nosibs_sub2 <- GSE_67_nosibs_sub1[complete.cases(GSE_67_nosibs_sub1),]
dim(GSE_67_nosibs_sub2) #68

MATCH_out <- matchit(Case1 ~ FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex+CEU,
                      method="nearest", distance="logit", discard="both",
                      ratio=2, caliper=.25,order="largest",data = GSE_67_nosibs_sub2)
sum_match <- summary(MATCH_out, interactions=T, standardize=T)
sum_match  ### only 16 and 12 matched
wt <- MATCH_out$weights
GSE_nosibs_match_data <- GSE_67_nosibs_sub2[wt>0,]
dim(GSE_nosibs_match_data) #28
summary(lm(ped94Age ~ Case1+FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex, data = GSE_nosibs_match_data)) #0.0338
summary(lm(ped94Age ~ Case1+FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex+CEU, data = GSE_nosibs_match_data)) #0.0369
GSE_nosibs_match_data$AgeAccel_nosibs_match  <- lm(ped94Age ~ FinalAge2+Buccal+SentrixID+BioSex+CEU, data = GSE_nosibs_match_data)$residuals
GSE_nosibs_match_data$Case2 <- gsub("0","TD",GSE_nosibs_match_data$Case1)
GSE_nosibs_match_data$Case2 <- gsub("1","ASD",GSE_nosibs_match_data$Case2)
ggplot(GSE_nosibs_match_data, aes(Case2, AgeAccel_nosibs_match))+
        geom_boxplot()+
        geom_point()
